# Testing standards

Use exactly three test types:

| Type | Rule |
|------|------|
| **UI** | Render **components** (not pages). Mock **services only** (GraphQL clients, `item/service`, `cart/service`, `review/service`, auth helpers). Client components that only call **server actions** may mock those action modules when there is no direct service import. Do **not** mock your own presentational components. |
| **Service** | Call **service** methods / server actions against real backends. **Real DB** (ItemsService Postgres; shopper tests start the ItemsService test server via `test/support/itemsService.ts`). **No mocks** for your database or service implementation. Third-party HTTP (login check) may be stubbed. |
| **Combined** | Render **pages** (`/`, `/login`, `/items/[id]`, etc.). Mock **third-party code only** (jose, cookie store, Next router, `@react-oauth/google`, Stripe, etc.). Do **not** mock anything you wrote (actions, services, internal components). |

## Layout

- `test/ui/` — component tests
- `test/service/` — service and action tests against real backends
- `test/combined/` — page tests
- Shared helpers in `test/support/`

## Quality

- Clear `describe` / `it` names that state behavior.
- Cover happy path, auth failures, and important error branches.
- Run `npm test` in the package you changed before finishing.
